To prove above propositions, the samples of S4 and S5 were carried out. PL intensity of S4 is over 2 times higher than that of S3 while S3 and S5 exhibit the almost same PL efficiency (Fig. 5
                     ). According to selective reduction of NaBH4 
                     [2,10], it can only reduce carbonyl and epoxy moieties and not carboxyl and amide-carbonyl groups to hydroxyl groups. Thus, N-related groups cannot enhance in S5, hardly improving PL efficiency. By contrast, S4 can obtain much more N-related groups since OH is easily extracted by ammonia on the basis of the mentioned above. In fact, EDS results also support our deduction. N content of S4 was up to 10.92wt% and its O content reduced to 4.79wt% while there were no obvious changes of N and O contents in S5.
